description: Lists the deployments in a deployment group for an application registered with the user or Amazon Web Services account.

parameters.name: applicationName
parameters.description: The name of an CodeDeploy application associated with the user or Amazon Web Services account.

parameters.name: deploymentGroupName
parameters.description: The name of a deployment group for the specified application.

parameters.name: includeOnlyStatuses
parameters.description: A subset of deployments to list by status: Created: Include created deployments in the resulting list. Queued: Include queued deployments in the resulting list. In Progress: Include in-progress deployments in the resulting list. Succeeded: Include successful deployments in the resulting list. Failed: Include failed deployments in the resulting list. Stopped: Include stopped deployments in the resulting list. (string) ---

parameters.name: createTimeRange
parameters.description: A time range (start and end) for returning a subset of the list of deployments. start (datetime) --- The start time of the time range. end (datetime) --- The end time of the time range.

nested_params.name: start
nested_params.description: The start time of the time range.

nested_params.name: end
nested_params.description: The end time of the time range.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If a large amount of information is returned, an identifier is also returned. It can be used in a subsequent list deployments call to return the next set of deployments in the list.
